records.addlTxt:
(2:16 PM cases 22CF494, 22CF623 called.) Prosecuting attorney Matthew Z Kirkpatrick in court for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant Justin D. Humphrey-Mickelson in court, in custody. Attorney Zebulon Patek in court for Justin D. Humphrey-Mickelson. 
Attorney Patek advises received a copy of the report and has discussed it with the defendant, no corrections or additions noted.
State moves for admission of the report and requests it be sealed. Attorney Patek has no objection. Court orders the report is received and is to be sealed.
Dr. Collins is present via video. Parties advise no testimony is needed and Dr. Collins may be released. Court releases Dr. Collins.
Attorney Patek advises is not objecting to the doctor's finding and requests outpatient treatment. 
State finds the report is sufficient and requests the defendant be found not competent to proceed at this time but likely to regain.
State requests the defendant be placed in an institution to restore competency.
Court finds the defendant is not competent to proceed at this time but likely to regain. 
Court finds there is no need for the involuntary administration of medication per the parties. Court orders there are 56 days of credit in 22CF494 and 53 days of credit in 22CF623.
